@NODE ABOUT "powerpc.library: About"
@NEXT SOFTWARE
With the AmigaOS4 powerpc.library it's possible to run WarpOS software
on AmigaOS4.


The powerpc.library functions are reimplemented using AmigaOS4
functions, it's not a WarpOS emulator, i.e. it doesn't emulate the
WarpOS kernel with an own task scheduler, mirror tasks, etc., nor the
lowlevel hardware drivers (warp[HW].library). 


With a few exceptions like NULL pointer accesses only system conforming
software can be used. Other bugs which might have been harmless on
AmigaOS 3.x will make broken WarpOS software crash on AmigaOS4 the same
way as broken m68k and AmigaOS4 software crashes. Unfortunately there is
a lot of broken WarpOS software, especially the scene demos. For
applications the proportion of broken WarpOS software is about the same
as for m68k software.


WarpOS software using Warp3D doesn't use Warp3D.library but needs a
Warp3DPPC.library instead. A Warp3DPPC.library which simply maps the
Warp3DPPC.library functions to the AmigaOS4 Warp3D.library is included,
but since it doesn't add features not included in the AmigaOS4 version
of Warp3D, nor includes workarounds for bugs in WarpOS Warp3D software,
a lot of old WarpOS Warp3D software doesn't work correctly on AmigaOS4,
especially on the Radeon gfx cards which weren't supported by the
AmigaOS 3.x version of Warp3D yet.

Most games support software 3D as well which usually works, and at least
on the AmigaOne that's fast enough since the games were written for the
much slower CyberStormPPC/BlizzardPPC systems and only needed hardware
3D to be usable on these slow systems.


Requirements:

AmigaOne, A4000 with CyberStormPPC, A1200 with BlizzardPPC or SAM440ep, with the current version of AmigaOS 4.x (at least the July 2007 update for the AmigaOne, February 2008 update for classic Amigas, AmigaOS 4.1 for the SAM440ep).
@{PAR}
@ENDNODE

@NODE GAMES "powerpc.library: Games"
@PREV SOFTWARE
Hints for getting some WarpOS games working on AmigaOS4.


@{B}FreeSpace@{UB}@{LINE}
- Disable Music.@{LINE}
- Disable Streamed Voice as well if you don't have a soundcard.@{LINE}
- Some gfx options have to enabled/disabled in the settings to get@{LINE}
  hardware 3D working correctly.


@{B}Heretic II@{UB}@{LINE}
- "Planar screens on RTG" has to be disabled in Prefs/GUI or@{LINE}
  rtgmaster.library crashes.@{LINE}
- Hardware 3D doesn't work correctly with most versions of@{LINE}
  W3D_Avenger.library (Voodoo3) nor on Radeon gfx cards.


@{B}Payback@{UB}@{LINE}
- On Radeon gfx cards there are some hardware 3D problems, using@{LINE}
  software 3D may be required.


@{B}Shogo@{UB}@{LINE}
- The CDDADEVICE and CDDAUNIT tooltypes have to be set or the launcher@{LINE}
  crashes in the m68k part. It doesn't have to be set to a DVD or CD@{LINE}
  drive, but the tooltypes have to be set, if they aren't set it does@{LINE}
  something wrong when searching for CD drives itself and crashes.@{LINE}
- Disable Music.@{LINE}
- Hardware 3D doesn't work correctly with any gfx card on AmigaOS4.@{LINE}
- You have to change the fonts in font.cfg, with the default@{LINE}
  Helvetica.font it only displays parts of the chars. For example using@{LINE}
  Arial Arial.font@{LINE}
  System Arial.font@{LINE}
  works, but probably using any outline font does.@{LINE}
  Arial TTF is availabe for free as part of the core fonts on@{LINE}
  http://sf.net/project/showfiles.php?group_id=34153&package_id=56408@{LINE}
  XAD (UnArc) can extract the .exe CAB archives.


@{B}WipeOut 2097@{UB}@{LINE}
- Disable MipMapping and the intro.@{LINE}
- You should reboot after playing the game.
@{PAR}
@ENDNODE

